SIMPLE: saturnalia
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Saturnalia
<hw>Sat`ur*na"li*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[L. See
<er>Saturn</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Rom. Antiq.)</fld> <def>The
festival of Saturn, celebrated in December, originally during one day,
but afterward during seven days, as a period of unrestrained license and
merriment for all classes, extending even to the slaves.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence: A period or occasion of general license, in
which the passions or vices have riotous indulgence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saturnalian</ent>⟦br⟧
